Rollback exercise: an isolated Pending-to-Passed fixture reproduces the raw
hash mismatch when status-neutral hashing is removed, then demonstrates that
normalization recovers the reviewed hash. Unsafe traversal, repository escape,
stale hashes, arbitrary report artifacts, and reviewer-role violations remain
negative cases in both runtimes.

CRLF regression: both status-neutral hash implementations preserve the original
line ending, and the parity fixture exercises CRLF Pending-to-Passed transitions.

Quality review cycle 2 regression: both runtimes reject contracts whose declared
attempt/round differs from the persisted report directory, per-reviewer missing
precheck or summary evidence, and case-changed canonical manifest paths. The
fixtures also verify that rejection occurs before downstream evidence is written.

Quality review cycle 3 regression: both runtimes select attempt 10 over attempt 9
by numeric generation ordering and reject a forged duplicate of an otherwise
allowed manifest path. Both adversarial cases fail before downstream evidence.

